This paper is likely to belong to the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) because it discusses the syntax and semantics of the input language of the ASP grounder GRINGO, which is a tool used in the field of AI for solving problems using Answer Set Programming. It may also belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) because it deals with the semantics of a programming language. Additionally, it may belong to the categories of Programming Languages (cs.PL), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Software Engineering (cs.SE) because it discusses constructs and specifications related to programming languages and software tools.
